headline.main: Study Suggests High Rate of Impotence

docs.lead_paragraph: THE largest study of impotence since the Kinsey report has found that about half of American men over 40 have experienced the problem to varying degrees. The federally financed study, carried out among 1,709 men in 11 areas in Massachusetts, asked them a variety of questions about their sexual potency during the previous six months.
